definition.value: A C14, long-chain fatty acid carrying an oxo- group at position 3.
A 3-hydroxy monocarboxylic acid consisting of cyclohexane carrying carboxymethyl and hydroxy substituents both at the 1-position.
A monocarboxylic acid consisting of cyclohexane carrying a carboxymethyl substituent.
A medium-chain fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of heptanoic acid.
An optically active form of 3-isopropenyl-6-oxoheptanoic acid having (3R)-configuration.
An optically active form of 3-isopropenyl-6-oxoheptanoic acid having (3S)-configuration.
An acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate that has the acyl group located at position 2 with an additional alkyl substituent at position 1.
An actinoid molecular entity containing at least one atome of thorium.
A monocarboxylic acid that is (E)-penta-2,4-dienoic acid substituted by a 1,3-benzodioxol-5-yl group at position 5. It has been isolated from black pepper (Piper nigrum).

The 6-O-methyl ether of erythromycin A, clarithromycin is a macrolide antibiotic used in the treatment of respiratory-tract, skin and soft-tissue infections. It is also used to eradicate Helicobacter pylori in the treatment of peptic ulcer disease. It prevents bacteria from growing by interfering with their protein synthesis.
